710472f-c.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 17th Street (West)
710472f-c.text:
Tenth Avenue, east side, south from W. 17th Street. Prominently
shown is the National Biscuit Company building. This occupies the
entire block east to 9th Avenue, from 16th to 15th S8reets. South
of same is a one story garae utilizing the 15th to 14th Street
frontage.
View 2 is limited to the National Biscuit Company Building.
No. 3 is the same view as No. 1 Photographed after partial de-
molition for the new elevated roadbed of the New York Central
Railroad. This will cross Tenth Avenue to continue on the east side
of same.
Views 1,2: July 16, 1932
View 3: September 6, 1933
P. L. Sperr
O REPREODUCTIOONS

710476f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 17th Street (West)
710476f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, north from W. 17th Street, showing Ihe
New York Central Railroad trains on the street level and a yard on
left. This feature, identifying this thoroughfare as ''Deaph or
Railroad Avenue'' is soon to be eliminated. An elevated roadbed will
be constructed to provide for same.
April 2, 1929

July 28, 1931
